pt sibling  recv vax 5SEP97 & 7OCT97 pt devel red bumps that extended to extremities & were heaviest on face;few lesions appeared on trunk, arms, & legs;10OCT97 seen by MD 25 lesions w/mult papules scattered;T100.2; 02/11/2010 Information has been received concernign a 20 weeks old male patient whose sibling was vaccinated on 05-SEP-1997 with VARIVAX. There was no concomitant medicationl On 07-OCT-1997 the patient developed "red bumps that extended to his extremities and were heaviest on his face". "A few" lesions also appeard on his trunk, arms and legs. On 10-OCT-1997 he was seen by a physician who noticed 25 lesions "with multiple papules scattered on his face, scalp, chest, abdomen, back and extremities". The patient also experienced a fever of 100.2 P rectually, but the infant was "otherwise fairly active and happy". Polymerase chain reaction analysis, obtained from a vesicle on his upper extremity, revealed VARIVAX/adequate specimen, vaccine strain. The patient's mother reported that the patient "bathed with the vaccinated sibling" who had a similar experience (WAES 97101013 and 97120340). Subsequently the patient's experiences were reported in a published literature article. The patient developed varicella after exposure to his sibling who was vaccinated with VARIVAX.
LAB_DATA: 10OCT97 Herpes simplex virus cul; 02/11/2010 Herpes simple virus, 10/10/97, OKA/Merck VIV/adequate speciment vaccine strain

Information has been received from a health care professional concerning a 29 month old Caucasian female with no known allergies and mild cold symptoms who on 30-SEP-1996 was vaccinated with one dose of VARIVAX. Concomitant vaccinations included the first dose of PROQUAD administered in left thigh and HIBTITER administered in right thigh. There were no other concomitant medications. On 01-DEC-1997 the patient was diagnosed with chickenpox. She subsequently experienced a secondary skin infection from scratching. The reporter described the case as moderate to severe. Subsequently, the patient recovered. No further information is available.

Information has been received from a physician concerning a 3 year old male patient who on 05-SEP-1997 was vaccinated with VARIVAX. On approximately 19-SEP-1997 the patient experienced "only two lesions both on his back". It was reported that "initially, the lesions looked like red dots and progressed to a pimple-like appearance" and the mother thought "they were bug bites". The lesions took "a long time to vesiculate, but once they scabbed over, they looked like typical chickenpox". The scabs "stayed on the vaccinee for approximately 10 to 14 days". It was reported that one of the patient's sibling had a similar experience (WAES 97101013 and 97120340). No further details were provided because the reporting physician had no additional information. Subsequently the patient's experience was reported in a published literature article. It was noted that the patient had two lesions and transmitted varicella to his sibling. No further information is expected.

This is in follow-up to report (s) previously submitted on 4/15/1998, 5/4/1999. Information has been received from a physician concerning a 24-month-old male with sickle cell trait ("HMG PAC THAL") who on 08-JAN-1998 was vaccianted with on dose of VARIVAX vaccube (lot # 623647/0802E) in his left arm. On 10-JAN-1998 the patient experienced a fever of 104 degrees F and had a febrile seizure. The patient was taken to an emergency room. It was noted that the patient's brother had been diagnosed with strep throat so a throat culture was obtained. The patient was released from the emergency room that same day. On 12-JAN-1998 the patient's throat culture was negative for strep throat. On 23-JAN-1998 the patient's mother calle the physicians' office to report that her son had experienced tremors while sleeping. The patient was scheduled for and EEg and was referred to a neurologist. "Within several weeks" after the initial experience, the patient again experienced another ferile seizure while in daycare. The patient was noted to have recovered. Additionally it was noted that the patient's mother did not follow through with the neurologist or the EEG appointments because "she believed the child's seizures were probably not related to the vaccine and that the child had probably caught a virus from his sibling. It was noted that the mother has since left the physician's practice. It was noted that another patient (WAES # 98011537) experienced a similar reaction after vaccination with VARIVAX vaccine. No further information is expected.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Information has been received from a health department coordinator concerning a 49-year-old male patient with a history of a tick bite in September 1990 who on 25AUG9? was vaccinated with RECOMBIVAX HB vaccine. On 01FEB93 the patient developed swelling in the joints of his fingers, arthralgia, itching in his legs, fatigue, loss of memory, lack of ability to concentrate, a rash with spots on his hands, one pupil was not able to fully dilate and he had loss of vision. Also, the patient experienced dizziness and -his balance was off". He was vaccinated with another dose of RECOMBIVAX HB vaccine on 24FEB93. Follow-up information received in June, 1997 revealed that the above experience "were seen soon after the completion of the RECOMBIVAX HB series". On 12MAY97 the patient was seen by a physician who "ruled out Lyme disease and diagnosed him with erythema multiforme". At the time of the report, the patient was "still being treated with prednisone for the swelling with some success". No further details were provided.

10 days p/vax pt exp fever 103, glands in neck very swollen, dizziness, myalgia & joint pain x 3 days;ongoing dizziness, fatigue;extreme dry mouth until present time. Information has been received from a consumer, a 41-year-old Caucasian female with a history of a fall in 1995 which resulted in "some" cervical damage, endometriosis, and an appendectomy who on 10-FEB-1998 was vaccinated SC with PROQUAD. Concomitant therapy included propoxyphene (+) acetaminophen. On 11-FEB-1998 the patient experienced a left dilated pupil. On 20-FEB-1998 the patient experienced a fever 104-105 degrees F x 2.5 days. At this time, the patient experienced severe shortness of breath, which lasted until April 1998. Additionally, the patient noted "right side of face and neck blew up." The swelling lasted for five days. The patient noted that the inside of her mouth peeled and that she had "no saliva." The patient noted that "the no saliva continues at this time." The patient sought unspecified medical treatment. A physician labeled the eye problem "Adie's Pupil" and said that it was related to a virus. In March 1998 the patient "was given steroids and had mononucleosis." In April 1998 "vision returned to the left eye." The patient further noted "right eye is now beginning to cause problems and will dilate and stay that way for about a day and then return to normal."The patient also has lost 40 pounds. Follow-up information from a physician indicated that the patient received PROQUAD in February, 1998. "After this, the patient developed facial edema and actually developed mumps and mononucleosis. Since that time the patient has had become more severely constiped and has lost 25 pounds, not purposely, although with the decreased salivation she is probably eating less. The patient does have odynophagia with the feeling and sensation of some discomfort of food going down her esphagus. The patient had one episode of vomiting, no nausea. She sometimes goes a week without having a bowel movement which is definitely a change for her. The patient has also seen some bright red blood in her stool which is also new. When her initial symptoms started in February, she had some shortness of breath as well. The patient had dyspnea on exertion and an echocardiogram and chest x-ray were done which were all normal. Additionally, it was noted that the patient's husband works with many pesticides and other chemicals and she does clean his clothes and is exposed to some of these chemicals. A physicain noted, "This is a somewhat interesting story which suggests some type of anticholinergic phenomenon, particularly given the constipation and dry mouth. Temporarily it seems to be related to the MMR shot, although I would have expected this to ohave resolved by now. GI wise, the weight loss is a problem, as is the new constipation and difficulty swallowing, again which may all be related to an anticholinergic effect, decreased salivation, etc. I am wondering about exposure to chemicals, particularly pesticides which may have some of her proble." Additional follow-up indicated that the patient is now on therapy with PROPULAID and is "not as constipated." Additional information has been requested.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: pt recv vax 29JUN93 & 4JUL94 exp a small sz;this may have been coincidental (since pt did have occasional small sz). The annual follow-up information obtained on 4/16/02 states that the pt is a vaccine injured child. At the age of four months pt experienced a status epilepticus grand mal seizure 8 1/2 hours after his DTP vaccine. This resulted in permanent brain damage. The complete extent of this damage was not realized until pt aged and experienced developmental delays. Pt's vaccine damage from teh DTP vaccine resulted in a seizure disorder. His seizures remained uncontrolled by medications. He also has autism, moderate mental retardation, ADHD, ETC as a result of this DTP vaccine. Pt has a small seizure 5 days after these injections since he did have an existing seizure disorder. This may have been coincidental. Pt's hyperactivity became so out of control after this time that he had to go on medications in Sept 1993 to help controlhis hyperactivity Aggression, impulsiveness, etc. We do not know if the vaccines may have had an effect on his hyperactivity increase. As of April 2002, pt remains  on medications for his hyperactivity and also remains on medications for his seizure.
HISTORY: sx disorder resulting from vax rxn @ 4mo;also has autism, ADHD mental retardation

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Six weeks post vax, pt lab eval revealed lack of seroconversion. This is in follow-up to report(s) previously submitted on 4/15/1998; 5/16/2000. Information has been received from a 28 year old female health care professional with negative VZV titers on 17-APR-1996 who on 07-MAY-1996 and 13-JUN-1996 was vaccinated with the first and second doses of VARIVAX SC in the left and right deltoids, respectively. On 07-AUG-1996 the patient sought unspecified medical attention and another serum VZV antibody test revealed a lack of seroconversion. No further information is available. This is an amended report. Case reference number 98000955-1 is a spontaneous report from a nurse referring to a female (nurse) aged 39 years. The patient has a history of allergy to ASA, NOVAHISTINE, MACROBID, and MARCODANTIN. The patient's past medical history included GRAVES disease and kidney stones. On 02-Dec-1997, the patient received the second treatment with ENERIX-B at dose unspecified. Approximately 12 hours later, on 03-Dec-1997, the patient developed arthralgia. On 04-Dec-1997, the patient developed nausea and fever (101-103 F). On 05-Dec-1997, the patient developed temperature of 104 F, nausea, vomiting, back and muscle pain, swollen joints, deep cough and wheezing. She was reportedly unable to move her legs without assistance. Treatment with VOLTAREN was reported to be not evvective. Treatment with DAYPRO was discontinued due to an allergic reaction. The patient was also treated with DARVOCET. As of 27-Jan-1998, the patient continues to have joint pain with some swelling, and muscle weakness. She continues ot run a low grade fever on occasion and had no appetite. The patient is reported to have no energy, needs a cane to ambulate, and has difficulty with daily avtivities. She is currently under the care of a rheumatologist. The most recent information receive on 28-Feb-1998 reports the outcome of the patient as ongoing.
HISTORY: allergy to ASA; MACROBID; MACRODANTIN; NOVAHISTINE; GRAVES disease, kidney stones;

pt recv vax APR98 & fatigue got worse;sed rate high;  Case, reference number 1998014677-1 is a spontaneous report from a patient's mother referring to a 12 year old daughter.  The patient has a history of environmental allergies.  At the time of the event, the patient was taking VANCENASE.  In September 1997, the patient received dose 1 of ENGERIX-B for prophylaxis of hepatitis B.  Subsequently, the patient experienced fatigue.  Dose 2 of ENGERIX-B was administered in October, 1997.  The fatigue continued through the second dose and almost resolved before the third dose.  Dose 3 of ENGERIX-B was administered in April, 1998.  The fatigue got worse after the third dose.  The patient missed five months of school due to fatigue and anrthralgias.  The patients mother did not connect the fatigue with the ENGERIX-B doses until after the third dose.  A doctor's visit was required.  No treatment was given.  In January, 1999, the patient had flu-like symptoms.  A mono test was positive at that time.  She was sick all summer, 1999 with joint pain, stomach pain, and profound fatigue.  Sed rate had been elevated and still was.  Gallium test was negative.  Rheumatologist suspected lupus, but dermatologist found no sign of this.  The patient is depressed at this time because of the inability to function normally.  Agency considers the adverse events experienced by this patient to be incapacitating.  The most recent information received on 15-DEC-99 reports the outcome of the patient as ongoing.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: pt recv vax & had a sz 14NOV98 taken to hosp;EEG & MRI was done w/negative results;MD advised observation next 2mo.  60 day follow up on 12/31/03: "Vaccine recipient did not recover from the adverse events that were reported for this vaccination.  Immediately after pt received the vaccine he came down with a cold, and at the time we thought it was just a cold bug that was going around.  We were not made aware of the fact that this could be one of the side effects of the vaccination.  It was within a couple of weeks that pt had his first seizure.  Now up until this point he was as healthy as a horse whose only illnesses were skinned knees and a smashed finger or two.  I realize information such as this is important in preventing this from happening again, but it is also important not to forget those who experienced the adverse reactions and since, had had to make changes in their lives and goals.  Pt has never recovered from this and to this day has to take medication to prevent seizures from happening again.  The next problem we have as a result of the medication he has to take, is dental problems.  The medication he is taking (dilantine) is taking it's toll on his teeth and gums.  Because of this it is very likely he will lose his teeth at a very early age.  As I said earlier, after pt received the vaccination there were changes in his disposition; he would become agitated easily and moody.  This we thought was because of the cold and like anybody else who gets a cold and who is not feeling good may just want to be left alone.  Now, we as parents did the right thing and pt also.  We abided by the rules and regulations and did what was asked.  Now our son needs your help.  Any assitance you can give would be greatly appreciated. " The hospital record received on 1/15/04 states sinusitis.
